Sometimes, you may want to have Keycloak connect to an external database rather than a database within your cluster - for example, when using a managed database service, or when running a single database server for all your applications.

To do so, specify credentials for the external database using the *externalDatabase* parameter. It is also necessary to disable the default PostgreSQL installation by setting the *postgresql.enabled` option to *false*. Here is an example:

    postgresql.enabled=false
    externalDatabase.host=myexternalhost
    externalDatabase.port=5432
    externalDatabase.user=myuser
    externalDatabase.password=mypassword
    externalDatabase.database=mydatabase

> NOTE: If you disable PostgreSQL per above, it is mandatory to supply values for the *externalDatabase.\** parameters.

